IMPRESSION
#1 Rectal cancer
I discussed the development, staging, and treatment of rectal cancer with Mr. and Mrs. Smith.  At this time, will proceed with staging chest x-ray, CT abdomen and pelvis, and endoscopic ultrasound.  The distal margin of the malignancy should be tattooed.  We discussed the need for chemoradiation if T3 or N1 disease is noted.  An Enterostomal Therapy consultation will be obtained for a diverting loop ileostomy education.  The patient will then meet with Colorectal Surgery for our recommendations.  She is referred specifically to Dr. Tomasini.
#2 Preoperative medical evaluation
Lab work, chest x-ray, and ECG are pending.  Once these are obtained and satisfactory, the patient is okay for anesthesia.
Discussed with Chris Presnell.  Note to follow.
